        <div class="msgSubject">How about a &quot;I'm Seeking Repairs&quot; Indicator Icon?</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-10 15:23:54   | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-128942423443794745" id="quote-128942423443794745" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-128942423443794745" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=173&amp;mid=128942423443794745&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=128942423443794745&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_128942423443794745" onclick="followToggle('add','128942423443794745')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Sage" href="/users/BrannonGalvalnor">BrannonGalvalnor</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Sage">Sage</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">80 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Excellent  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">I'll apologize if this has been already posted, but I thought it would be a good idea if we have to constantly put up with needing to repair our gear to get the maxiumum benefit out of our stuff.  You know how when we're looking to sell our goods or seeking to buy specific stuff? We bazaar it (on ourselves or our retainers) and then you see the little <u>bag icon</u> next to the name indicating that person wants to deal with some selling and/or buying. <br /> <br />How about we have a <b>UNIQUE</b> <u>repair needed icon</u> next to the name, <i><b>specifically</b></i> for people seeking repairs? <br /> <br />I don't really understand SE's thinking when they decided to lump seeking repairs with bazaaring.  I know when we target a person, they may have a yellow or red sword/shield icon, under their name, indicating they are wearing damaged gear, but that doesn't mean they have the damaged gear put up and asking for repairs. Plus, we still don't have the option to repair stuff while the person is wearing it.  Plus, visually speaking, it's <i><b>FASTER</b></i> for me to skim through a crowd of people and see the icon next to their name indicating what they want.  <br /> <br />The key here with this idea is to help people get their stuff repaired faster when they don't have a friend online who can help them or requiring constant /shouting around, asking for someone to repair their stuff.  It'll also help crafters who want to make a little Gil and skillup their trade by having those people seeking repairs, immediately pointed out.  If they are just seeking only repairs, make the icon a little Hammer with an Exclaimation mark next to their name.  Reminiscent of the old FF11 &quot;I'm open for invite!&quot; days. If SE has concern about the limitations about how many icons can appear next to a person's name (currently I've only seen various linkshell badges, bazaar icons, and the occasional AFK or Red Circle-Disconnect), add a little hammer crossing over the bazaar bag icon to indicate they are seeking repairs and selling/buying goods. <br /> <br />Another suggestion I would like SE to implement, but may be more difficult to do (due to repairs  can fail and consuming the repair material), is have the person seeking repairs to lump-in/provide the material that is needed, into the transaction, to repair their gear.  Not every Crafter has Gil weighing down their pockets nor do they have some of the rare material that is needed for some repairs.  As I've read some other threads concerning repairing, asking someone to repair your gear for less than the value of the repair material is unfair to the crafter, but if it was just skill alone that was required, then there would probably be more crafters up and around to help people repair their stuff, cheaply, if they didn't have to spend a ton of gil on the repair materials. <br /> <br /><u>TLDR:</u> Make a unique icon for people who need gear repaired, appear next to their name.  Make it easier for them to be spotted thus, crafters seeking to repair people's gear for skillups and profit find them easier and faster. Everyone wins. <br /> <br />What do you guys think?<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Consciousness - That annoying time between naps.</div></div>
